format: A data frame with 192 observations on the following 5 variables.
reference:
For each of the three species mungbean, rice, and wheat, a total of 20 seeds were uniformly distributed on filter paper in a petri dish (diameter: 9.0cm) 
and then placed in dark climate cabinets with different temperatures (10, 16, 22, 28, 34, 40 degrees Celsius). Not all of the temperatures were applied to all species. 
The germinated seeds were counted and removed from the petri dish on a daily basis up to 18 days (or until all seeds had germinated). I
title: Germination of three crops
description:
Description
Germination data were obtained from experiments involving the three species mungbean, rice, and wheat, which were opposed
to different temperatures between 10 and 40 degrees Celsius. Experiments lasted at most 18 days.

parameters.start: a numeric vector of left endpoints of the monitoring intervals
parameters.germinated: a numeric vector giving the numbers of seeds germinated
parameters.temp: a numeric vector of temperatures that seeds were exposed to
parameters.end: a numeric vector of right endpoints of the monitoring intervals
parameters.species: a factor with levels mungbean rice wheat
